<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4664751>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 2. — A-C, E, F, Tympanicysta stoschiana Balme from the basal Vetlugian of Nedubrovo and Sholga, Vologda region; A, vegetative cell showing chloroplast and infolded septa at the top; B, vegetative cells with infolded septae; C, swollen terminal cell; E, akinete-like cell; F, vegetative filament; D, Spirogyra sp., extant, from a floating mat of a floodplain pond, Bitsa River, the Moscow River Basin, collected in June 1999, vegetative filament at transition to akinete. Scale bars: A, B, D, E, 10 µm; C, 20 µm; F, 30 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4664751/files/figure.png" .

